 <text id="A2570T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Hotchkiss continues a previous letter, describing camp life and giving instruction concerning
     food at home.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
     </dateline>
     <salute/>
    </opener>

    <p>I must now go to my cold bed -- and wake up cold in the morning -- the worst part of camp
     life -- but I can stand it, and will not complain, when thousands are worse off than I am -- I
     was going to say infinitely -- I write to Nelson to have some meal &amp; hominy ground --
     It don't matter much <orig reg="about">abut</orig> the hominy if not easily procured -- May the
     God of peace be with you all &amp; bless you -- Good night, my love -- pleasant dreams to
     you &amp; refreshing slumbers -- </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Your husband</salute>
     <signed>Jed. H--</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
